The White House Press Secretary released a statement on May 2, 2010, regarding the President's update on the Times Square incident. The President was updated at around 10:45 PM and commended the quick action taken by the NYPD. He also asked John Brennan to inform the NYPD that the federal government is ready to offer support. Brennan, along with the NYPD and others, will continue to keep the President informed on the progress of the investigation.